description: A Software Engineer is responsible for designing, developing, testing, and maintaining software applications. They work closely with product teams to understand requirements and translate them into technical specifications.

A Product Designer focuses on creating intuitive and user-friendly interfaces for digital products. They research user needs, conduct usability testing, and collaborate with developers to bring designs to life.

A Product Manager is responsible for the overall success of a product. They define the product vision, gather customer feedback, and work with cross-functional teams to ensure the product meets market needs and business objectives.

An HR professional oversees various aspects of human capital management, including recruitment, onboarding, employee relations, performance management, and benefits administration. They ensure compliance with labor laws and promote a positive work environment.
A QA Engineer is responsible for ensuring the quality of software products. They develop and execute test plans, identify and report defects, and work with developers to resolve issues.
